xxl.core.relational.tuples

Class WrappedTuple

  • java.lang.Object
    • xxl.core.relational.tuples.AbstractTuple
      • xxl.core.relational.tuples.WrappedTuple
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Tuple
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ProjectedTuple

    public class WrappedTuple
extends AbstractTuple
    This class provides an extended decorator for tuples. Calls to the methods of this class (getXXX(int column)) are redirected to the wrapped instance (getXXX(originalColumnIndex(column))). Note, that the given column index of the original method call is substituded by a mapped column index. This mapping, performed by the originalColumnIndex method, can be easily used to create smaller or even reordered tuples without creating a new one and storing the interesting values a second time. (In the case of smaller tuples, the getColumnCount method must also be overwritten to return the correct number of remaining columns.)
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
